  "text": "A third and final issue is that while current data speak to an absence of effects of adolescent fluoxetine treatment on a variety of standard measures of anxiety-/fear-/stress-related behaviors, it would be premature to exclude potential effects of the same treatment on other behavioral processes. In this context, increased suicidal ideation, aggression, and impulsivity are reported to be abnormal in a subpopulation of SRI-treated children [CITATION_1] Usala et al. 2007; [CITATION_2] ). It will therefore be of importance to examine the effects of adolescent fluoxetine treatment on phenotypic measures such as conspecific aggression and executive functions (e.g., see [CITATION_3] .",
